49:27.609 --> 49:29.644
You in the sticks
or are you in town?

49:29.678 --> 49:31.479
Almost in town.

49:31.513 --> 49:33.615
Okay, come by the Bullfrog.

49:33.648 --> 49:34.783
Why?

49:34.816 --> 49:36.584
'Cause I fucking
said so, Boon.

49:36.618 --> 49:37.752
Drop the shit attitude.

49:38.653 --> 49:39.888
I want you to take Hutch.

49:40.990 --> 49:43.125
No, no, no, I got this.

49:43.159 --> 49:45.194
I'll have the kid and
the ruby within the hour,

49:45.227 --> 49:48.496
and then you can have your
little talk with him, right.

49:49.564 --> 49:50.966
You know what?

49:51.000 --> 49:52.600
How about you do me a favor

49:52.634 --> 49:54.569
and pretend like I'm
still the fucking boss

49:54.602 --> 49:55.804
at least for one more day?

49:55.837 --> 49:58.673
Come get Hutch, then
you two go grab the kid.

49:58.707 --> 50:00.142
You got it?

50:00.176 --> 50:01.010
The baby.

50:05.147 --> 50:07.716
Yes, he's just an asshole.

50:07.749 --> 50:08.650
Yes, he is.

50:47.123 --> 50:48.157
Put it out.

50:55.197 --> 50:56.132
Let's go.

51:05.141 --> 51:06.142
So what now?

51:07.243 --> 51:09.577
I know where he's going.

51:10.745 --> 51:12.680
Well, how's that?

51:14.016 --> 51:16.352
You've been looking for
him since this morning.

51:16.385 --> 51:18.753
He's running out of
places to go in this town,

51:18.787 --> 51:19.654
and he's a kid.

51:21.723 --> 51:22.590
Yeah.

51:23.825 --> 51:26.228
Well, he's a little
shit is what he is,

51:26.262 --> 51:28.930
just like his stupid brother.

51:28.963 --> 51:30.598
Fucking stupid.

51:30.632 --> 51:31.766
The kid's not stupid.

51:32.867 --> 51:37.173
He's angry, he's scared,
but he's not stupid.

51:45.780 --> 51:48.150
Well, let's make this quick.

51:49.651 --> 51:50.919
You got some place to be?

51:52.787 --> 51:55.057
No, but you do.

51:57.293 --> 51:58.160
Don't you?

52:00.029 --> 52:01.930
Don't you got a funeral
to go to, right?

52:16.979 --> 52:18.780
After you.

52:24.453 --> 52:25.753
Shitty motel room.

52:27.189 --> 52:28.723
Sure you're not a perv?

52:28.756 --> 52:31.160
Yeah, well, I gotta
stay off the grid, son.

52:31.193 --> 52:33.095
Local law enforcement
doesn't even know I'm here

52:33.129 --> 52:34.863
and I intend to
keep it that way.

52:36.298 --> 52:37.433
Besides you're not my type,

52:37.466 --> 52:39.634
I like 'em blonde
and double D's.

52:42.704 --> 52:45.773
Now the last time I saw your
brother was early this morning,

52:45.807 --> 52:48.310
he was supposed to
finalize a deal with me,

52:49.478 --> 52:51.913
but I guess he had
a change of heart.

52:51.946 --> 52:53.715
Then I track you down, and uh.

53:01.390 --> 53:03.758
Do you know where your
brother's at, Motley?

53:07.163 --> 53:08.963
You need to listen
to me very carefully

53:08.998 --> 53:10.065
'cause the man your brother

53:10.099 --> 53:12.901
works for is
extremely dangerous.

53:12.934 --> 53:16.871
He won't give two thoughts to
killing you, your mom, Emily,

53:18.274 --> 53:21.010
so if you know something,
anything at all about your brother

53:22.111 --> 53:23.778
now would be a good
time to tell me.

53:35.224 --> 53:39.328
Jed Haywood ran a crew in
Mississippi back in '89, '90,

53:39.361 --> 53:41.829
that was the first time
I'd ever heard of him.

53:43.165 --> 53:47.702
You know, in my line of work
sometimes you see things

53:49.071 --> 53:50.939
that, that stick with you,
things you can't shake.

53:52.874 --> 53:55.144
I remember I was stationed there

53:55.177 --> 53:57.146
for a few weeks working a case,

53:57.179 --> 53:59.847
hell, I can't even
remember what the case was,

54:01.350 --> 54:02.750
but I do remember the morning

54:02.784 --> 54:04.486
we went to Lester
Bowman's apartment.

54:12.228 --> 54:14.896
You see Lester worked with Jed,

54:16.532 --> 54:18.866
and he saw something
that made him turn,

54:20.935 --> 54:22.837
so we went to get
him that morning.

54:24.173 --> 54:27.343
I, I just remember all
the blood, the, the smell.

54:29.578 --> 54:33.015
Lester, his mom, his twin
sisters, even their cat.

54:40.990 --> 54:41.856
Here.

54:47.129 --> 54:52.101
So uh, son, you can
protect your family,

54:53.002 --> 54:54.869
just tell me what happened.

55:01.443 --> 55:03.078
Danny's dead.

55:03.112 --> 55:03.979
They killed him.

55:05.847 --> 55:06.881
No.

55:06.914 --> 55:09.351
Damn, son, I'm, I'm sorry.

55:12.221 --> 55:13.088
Uh.

55:18.960 --> 55:23.465
Yeah, this morning he
was gonna pick me up,

55:23.499 --> 55:28.504
and uh, and we, and
then we were leaving,

55:30.172 --> 55:33.208
and then uh, if he
never picked me up

55:33.242 --> 55:35.077
he, he probably would be alive.

55:38.614 --> 55:40.215
Hey, it's okay.

55:41.650 --> 55:42.584
It's okay.

55:42.618 --> 55:45.354
Look, you'll be all right.

55:46.954 --> 55:50.225
Listen to me, son, what
I'm about to ask you

55:50.259 --> 55:53.329
it's very important
for you to answer me

55:53.362 --> 55:54.496
and tell me the truth.

55:56.465 --> 55:58.033
Did you see your brother die?

56:03.938 --> 56:06.508
Motley, I can get
you and your mom safe

56:06.542 --> 56:08.043
but you gotta tell me now.

56:11.580 --> 56:12.448
And Emily?

56:14.149 --> 56:17.952
Yes, and Emily too.

56:20.356 --> 56:22.890
Did you see Jed Haywood
kill your brother?

56:30.232 --> 56:31.233
See you tomorrow.

56:53.188 --> 56:54.323
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

56:54.356 --> 56:55.190
What are you doing?

56:55.224 --> 56:56.291
Let go of me!

56:56.325 --> 56:58.293
- Shut the fuck up!
- Let go of me! Let go of me!

56:58.327 --> 56:59.395
What are you doing?

56:59.428 --> 57:00.295
Help!

57:00.329 --> 57:01.330
Help, help!

57:02.231 --> 57:03.532
Please help!

57:03.565 --> 57:04.466
Help me!

57:17.513 --> 57:19.047
What do you want?

57:30.626 --> 57:35.330
What did uh, Danny tell
the feds, sweetheart?

57:40.369 --> 57:41.737
What?

57:41.770 --> 57:43.472
What?

57:43.505 --> 57:45.407
